14 WHEREAS, Sheriff Terry Deese's efficient and effective commitment to excellence has been
15 recognized by his peers through the many decorations and awards he has received, including
16 earning the 2017 Sheriff of the Year and the 2012 Trailblazer Award from Fort Valley State
17 University; and
18 WHEREAS, his inspiring commitment to the welfare of others is an outstanding example of
19 the positive effect law enforcement professionals have on the lives and well-being of others;
20 and
21 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that gratitude is expressed for the unique and
22 often unheralded contributions of local law enforcement professionals on behalf of the
23 citizens of this state.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
25 the members of this body commend the care, courage, sympathy, and selfless dedication
26 exhibited by Sheriff Terry Deese in carrying out the difficult duties of his vocation,
27 congratulate him upon the grand occasion of his retirement, and express their utmost
28 appreciation for having so purely and truly defined for others the meaning of public servant.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
30 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
31 Sheriff Terry Deese.
